This snapshot Released In Friday March 13 2026

1 Added Fastfetch (Compile It From Source)

1 Install Dependencies

sudo apt update
sudo apt install git cmake build-essential pkg-config \
    libdrm-dev libpci-dev libx11-dev libwayland-dev

2 Clone the Repository

git clone https://github.com/fastfetch-cli/fastfetch.git
cd fastfetch

3. Configure the Build

mkdir build && cd build
cmake ..

You can enable optional features with flags, for example:

cmake .. -DENABLE_VULKAN=ON -DENABLE_OPENCL=ON

4. Compile

make -j$(nproc)

5. Install (Optional)

sudo make install

After installation, simply run:

fastfetch

2 Removed Snapd

1 You May Stop The Services Of Snap
  sudo systemctl stop snapd
  sudo systemctl disable snapd

2 Purge Snapd (Recommended For Older Hardware Or Any Slow Hardware)
  sudo apt purge snapd

3 Clean Up Leftover Directories
  rm -rf ~/snap
  sudo rm -rf /var/snap /var/lib/snapd /var/cache/snapd

4 Reboot
  sudo reboot

5 System Updates: Ubuntu may reinstall Snapd during major upgrades. To prevent this, you can block Snapd from being reinstalled:
  sudo apt-mark hold snapd

3 git clone is now recommended for Triaxis GNU/Linux
